  "prompt": "Can a killer whale eat a stingray?",
  "response": "Yes, killer whales, also known as orcas, are known to eat a variety of marine animals, including stingrays. Their diet can vary significantly depending on their specific population and location, but many orcas are opportunistic feeders and will prey on available species, which can include fish, squid, seals, and even stingrays. Their strong jaws and sharp teeth allow them to capture and eat a wide range of prey.",
